  "text": "We examined 47 formalin-fixed and paraffin-embedded specimens of OSCC obtained from patients who underwent surgical treatment in the Department of Cranio-Maxillofacial and Oncological Surgery. 26 cases were from males and 21 from females. The mean age of patients was 55 years. There were selected samples of well [CITATION_1] , moderately [CITATION_2] and poorly differentiated (4) OSCC. Additionally, tissue specimens from 12 cases of uninvolved oral mucosa were chosen as controls.",
